⊕meta⊕
name = "check-sky-environment"
description = "Preflight doctor: probe the local sky environment (claude CLI, gh auth, git remote reachability, daemon health, declared-but-unset secrets) and report OK/WARN/FAIL per check, exiting non-zero on any FAIL. Pure bash."
params.dir.type = "string"
params.dir.required = true
params.dir.description = "Workflow library directory whose .sky files are scanned for declared secrets."
trigger.manual = true
output_style = "terse"
ui = "ui/workflow"
⊕⊕

※probe※
Bash root node. Runs every environment check and prints one `OK|WARN|FAIL <check>: <detail>` line per probe plus a summary; exits non-zero when any check FAILs so CI and dashboards see red.
※※

§probe§
bash_file = "./scripts/probe.sh"
§§

※※
check-sky-environment — preflight doctor for a sky install

One pure-bash node, no LLM cost.

Checks (in order):
  1. skyway version           OK   (informational)
  2. claude CLI on PATH       FAIL when missing — nothing LLM-shaped can run
  3. gh present + gh auth     FAIL when present-but-unauthenticated, WARN when absent
  4. git repo + origin        FAIL when origin is unreachable, WARN when absent
  5. daemon GET /health       WARN when down — manual runs still work, schedules/webhooks do not
  6. secrets[] vs env         FAIL per env var declared in any {{dir}}/**.sky secrets[] but unset

Run:
  skyway run check-sky-environment --var dir=.sky/workflows

Vars:
  dir  directory scanned for .sky files (secrets check); required

Notes:
  - Complements GET /api/workflows/health (daemon-side lint + MCP probes); this covers
    the host environment the daemon cannot see from inside a request.
  - Daemon base URL honors $SKY_SERVER_URL, default http://localhost:3090.
  - Read-only: no file is written, nothing is mutated.
※※
